ANC top officials will look at matters arising from the party’s Women’s League President, Bathabile Dlamini’s conviction of perjury. A Task Team appointed by the ANC’s National Working Committee, led by Thandi Modise, has mandated top officials to make sure that action is taken in accordance with the party’s policies to determine her future in the league. The Task Team will be looking at the build-up to the ANC Women’s League national conference and the legitimacy of its national executive committee. ANC Treasurer-General Paul Mashatile was briefing the media on the outcomes of the ANC NEC meeting over the weekend. “It mandated the officials and the NWC to process the report of the Task Team and take decisions to be reported to the ANC NEC for ratification. Furthermore, it mandates the national officials to attend to matters arising from the conviction of the ANC Women’s League President Bathabile Dlamini in line with ANC policy.” ANC media briefing below: